                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-22T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>337. Departments October 31, 8 p.m.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to again call the attention of the Chinese Government to the
                    continuing default on the Chicago Continental Bank loan and insist that some
                    immediate action be taken to remedy the <pb facs="0510" n="386" xml:id="pg_386"
                    /> present wholly unsatisfactory condition. Please call attention to the fact
                    that since November 1st, the date on which default occurred, China has paid
                    interest on subsequently maturing obligations and that fact has created further
                    misunderstanding on the part of American investors holding China’s defaulted
                    notes. You may suggest that if it is impossible for the Chinese Government to
                    pay principal at this time, it would have beneficial effect upon Chinese credit
                    if past due interest were paid pending arrangements to pay principal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
